definition.value: An organic heteroheptacyclic compound consisting of a xanthene ring system fused with two octahydro-2H-quinolizine units.
Tropine substituted at oxygen by an acyl group.
Pseudotropine substituted at oxygen by an acyl group.
A fluorescein compound having chlorine substituents in the 2'-, 4-, 7- and 7'-positions and a succinimidyloxycarbonyl substituent at the 6-position.
A nanocrystalline cadmium telluride fluorescent dye with an emission wavelength of 680 nm.
A nanocrystalline fluorescent dye with an emission wavelength of 520 nm.
A fluorescent dye of absorption wavelength 495 nm and emission wavelength 519 nm, derived from a 3,6-diaminoxanthenium-4,5-disulfate.
The 6-isomer of Alexa Fluor 488.
The 5-isomer of Alexa-Fluor 488.
A fluorescent dye of absorption wavelength 517 nm and emission wavelength 542 nm derived from a 3,6-diaminoxanthenium-4,5-disulfate.
The 6-succinimidyloxycarbonyl isomer of Alexa Fluor 514.
The 5-succinimidyloxycarbonyl isomer of Alexa Fluor 514.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 1,4-dihydroxy-2-naphthoic acid.
A heptanoic acid having an amino-substituent at the 2-position, hydroxy-substituents at the 4- and 5-positions, an oxo-substituent at the 6-position and a phosphonooxy-substituent at the 7-position.
A 2-hydroxy-substituted benzohydrazide having a hexanoyl group at the N'-position
An undefined naphthalenecarbonyl group
A fluorescent dye of absorption wavelength 555 nm and emission wavelength 565 nm, derived from a 3,6-diaminoxanthene-4,5-disulfate.
A nanocrystal consisting of cadmium telluride.
A naphthoyl group having the carbonyl substituent in the 2-position.
A naphthoyl group having the carbonyl substituent in the 1-position.
A fluorescent dye of absorption wavelength 612 nm and emission wavelength 628 nm, derived from a heteropentacyclic ring system.
A member of the class of phenols that is phenol having a methoxy-substituent at the 3-position.
A resorcinol compound having an alkyl substituent at the 5-position.
A resorcinol compound having an 8-cis,11-cis-pentadeca-8,11,14-trien-1-yl substituent at the 5-position.
A phenol compound having a methoxy substituent at the 3-position and a 8-cis,11-cis-pentadeca-8,11,14-trien-1-yl substituent at the 5-position.
A butanediol in which the two hydroxy groups are located at positions 1 and 2.
A butanediol compound having two hydroxy groups in the 1- and 3-positions.
A member of the class of butanediols that is butane in which two of the hydrogens have been replaced by hydroxy groups.
A butane-1,2-diol of R-configuration.
A butane-1,2-diol of S-configuration.
A butane-1,3-diol of R-configuration.
A butane-1,3-diol of S-configuration.

A 2',7'-bis-(2-carboxyethyl)carboxyfluorescein compound having a carboxy substituent in the 6-position.
A BODIPY dye having a phenyl substituent at the 5-position and a (2-carboxyethyl) substituent at the 3-position.
A BODIPY dye conjugated to the bicyclic peptide phallacidin via an amide linkage.
A C3 cyanine dye having 1-ethyl-3,3-dimethylindoleinine units at each end.
A xanthene dye-based amide comjugate.
A xanthene dye-based thiourea conjugate.

A benzoic acid compound having an iodosyl substituent at the ortho-position.
A benziodoxole compound having a hydroxy substituent at the 1-position and an oxo substituent at the 3-position.
A benzoic acid compound having an iodyl substituent at the ortho-position.

A benziodoxole compound having hydroxy and oxo substituents at the 1-position and an oxo substituent at the 3-position. It is a mild and efficient hypervalent iodine synthetic reagent used to carry out several selective oxidation reactions.
A heteroyclic compound having as ring members atoms of carbon and iodine.
